=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Resonz_ex2 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright mixed sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 1563 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and impulsive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: impulsive
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 1563.4559
  harmonic_decay_rate: -1.6796
  harmonic_regularity: 0.7449
  pitch_clarity: 6.9991
  inharmonicity: 0.1689
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -17.5411
  resonance_freq: 2605.5176

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Resonz Example 2
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Resonz.html
// Tags: Resonz, Classes, filter
// ---
// --- Example 2 ---
{ Resonz.ar(WhiteNoise.ar(0.5), 2000, 0.1) }.play

// modulate frequency
{ Resonz.ar(WhiteNoise.ar(0.5), XLine.kr(1000, 8000, 10), 0.05) }.play

// modulate bandwidth
{ Resonz.ar(WhiteNoise.ar(0.5), 2000, XLine.kr(1, 0.001, 8)) }.play

// modulate bandwidth opposite direction
{ Resonz.ar(WhiteNoise.ar(0.5), 2000, XLine.kr(0.001, 1, 8)) }.play
